<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,971,1141]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,971,996]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elongate, shiny, smooth, and glabrous species. Head with a distinct neck; antennal segment II six times longer than segment I. Pronotum clearly narrowed anteriorly; embolium-corial and clavo-corial sutures without punctures. Scutellum smooth (without slender, erect process as in the Old World 
<taxonomicName authority="Signoret" authorityName="Signoret" box="[1082,1306,1044,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Helopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1197,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Helopeltis</emphasis>
Signoret
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum and hemelytra glabrous; apical angle of areole on membrane rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,971,1141]" box="[199,1196,1116,1141]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Carvalho (
<number box="[316,374,1116,1140]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1972.0">1972</number>
) revised this genus. Only one species is known to occur in Minas Gerais.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
